  "bookId": 24,
  "firstAcquaintance": "A rat-kin chef girl who always carries a huge backpack. The food inside her bag seems like it could never run out.",
  "personality": "Cheerful and optimistic, always thinking about food. She is very loyal to her friends and will immediately jump in to protect anyone she knows when they are in trouble.",
  "like": "Gourmet food",
  "familiarData": "Mozarela is a gluttonous rat-kin girl. She holds demon federation citizenship and lives a decent life, but left town to become a wandering chef in search of gourmet food.\nShe habitually carries a giant backpack filled with ingredients she has gathered. Thanks to the rat-kin's natural poison resistance, rotten meat, poisonous meat, toxic mushrooms, and wild grass all become ingredients for her cooking.\nShe met a wanderer group in the wilderness and often trades beast meat for flour and milk. However, sometimes she encounters wicked wanderers who try to steal her large bag of ingredients. But since most of the bag's contents are toxic, it ends up causing mass food poisoning instead.\nMozarela has excellent cooking skills, but unfortunately most of her ingredients are somewhat toxic so she cannot share her food with others. Quartz and Roland are among the few who can eat her cooking.\nDon't underestimate her innocent appearance. Her punches are surprisingly heavy, and being hit by her body feels like being charged by a large beast. Also, it is best not to casually call her fat -- she can be quite dangerous when angered.",
